     fhir:Narrative.div "<div xml:lang=\"en\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" lang=\"en\"><p class=\"res-header-id\"><b>Narratif généré : CodeSystem v3-ObservationMethod</b></p><a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod\"> </a><a name=\"hcv3-ObservationMethod\"> </a><div style=\"display: inline-block; background-color: #d9e0e7; padding: 6px; margin: 4px; border: 1px solid #8da1b4; border-radius: 5px; line-height: 60%\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px\">version : 1; Dernière mise à jour : 2026-01-07 10:12:51+0100; Langue : en</p></div><p><b>Propriétés</b></p><p><b>Cette terminologie de référence (CodeSystem) définit les propriétés suivantes pour ses concepts</b></p><table class=\"grid\"><tr><td><b>Nom</b></td><td><b>Code</b></td><td><b>URI</b></td><td><b>Type</b></td><td><b>Description</b></td></tr><tr><td>internalId</td><td>internalId</td><td>http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/utg-concept-properties#v3-internal-id</td><td>code</td><td>The internal identifier for the concept in the HL7 Access database repository.</td></tr><tr><td>status</td><td>status</td><td>http://hl7.org/fhir/concept-properties#status</td><td>code</td><td>Designation of a concept's state.  Normally is not populated unless the state is retired..</td></tr><tr><td>howApplies</td><td>howApplies</td><td>http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/utg-concept-properties#v3-how-applies</td><td>string</td><td>Haven't a clue!</td></tr><tr><td>Not Selectable</td><td>notSelectable</td><td>http://hl7.org/fhir/concept-properties#notSelectable</td><td>boolean</td><td>Indicates that the code is abstract - only intended to be used as a selector for other concepts</td></tr></table><p><b>Concepts</b></p><p>This case-sensitive code system <code>http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/v3-ObservationMethod</code> defines the following codes dans une hiérarchie Is-A:</p><table class=\"codes\"><tr><td><b>Niv</b></td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\"><b>Code</b></td><td><b>Affichage</b></td><td><b>Définition</b></td><td><b>internalId</b></td><td><b>status</b></td><td><b>howApplies</b></td><td><b>Not Selectable</b></td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">_DecisionObservationMethod<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-_DecisionObservationMethod\"> </a></td><td>DecisionObservationMethod</td><td><div><p>Provides codes for decision methods, initially for assessing the causality of events.</p>\n</div></td><td>21094</td><td>active</td><td/><td>true</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  ALGM<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-ALGM\"> </a></td><td>algorithm</td><td><div><p>Reaching a decision through the application of an algorithm designed to weigh the different factors involved.</p>\n</div></td><td>19992</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>3</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">    BYCL<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-BYCL\"> </a></td><td>bayesian calculation</td><td><div><p>Reaching a decision through the use of Bayesian statistical analysis.</p>\n</div></td><td>19993</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  GINT<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-GINT\"> </a></td><td>global introspection</td><td><div><p>Reaching a decision by consideration of the totality of factors involved in order to reach a judgement.</p>\n</div></td><td>19991</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">_GeneticObservationMethod<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-_GeneticObservationMethod\"> </a></td><td>GeneticObservationMethod</td><td><div><p>A code that provides additional detail about the means or technique used to ascertain the genetic analysis. Example, PCR, Micro Array</p>\n</div></td><td>22644</td><td>active</td><td/><td>true</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  PCR<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-PCR\"> </a></td><td>PCR</td><td><div><p><strong>Description:</strong> Polymerase Chain Reaction</p>\n</div></td><td>22645</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">_ObservationMethodAggregate<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-_ObservationMethodAggregate\"> </a></td><td>observation method aggregate</td><td><div><p>Provides additional detail about the aggregation methods used to compute the aggregated values for an observation. This is an abstract code.</p>\n</div></td><td>23444</td><td>active</td><td/><td>true</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  AVERAGE<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-AVERAGE\"> </a></td><td>average</td><td><div><p>Average of non-null values in the referenced set of values</p>\n</div></td><td>23447</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  COUNT<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-COUNT\"> </a></td><td>count</td><td><div><p>Count of non-null values in the referenced set of values</p>\n</div></td><td>23445</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  MAX<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-MAX\"> </a></td><td>maxima</td><td><div><p>Largest of all non-null values in the referenced set of values.</p>\n</div></td><td>23453</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  MEDIAN<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-MEDIAN\"> </a></td><td>median</td><td><div><p>The median of all non-null values in the referenced set of values.</p>\n</div></td><td>23454</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  MIN<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-MIN\"> </a></td><td>minima</td><td><div><p>Smallest of all non-null values in the referenced set of values.</p>\n</div></td><td>23452</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  MODE<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-MODE\"> </a></td><td>mode</td><td><div><p>The most common value of all non-null values in the referenced set of values.</p>\n</div></td><td>23455</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  STDEV.P<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-STDEV.46P\"> </a></td><td>population standard deviation</td><td><div><p>Standard Deviation of the values in the referenced set of values, computed over the population.</p>\n</div></td><td>23450</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  STDEV.S<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-STDEV.46S\"> </a></td><td>sample standard deviation</td><td><div><p>Standard Deviation of the values in the referenced set of values, computed over a sample of the population.</p>\n</div></td><td>23448</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  SUM<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-SUM\"> </a></td><td>sum</td><td><div><p>Sum of non-null values in the referenced set of values</p>\n</div></td><td>23446</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  VARIANCE.P<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-VARIANCE.46P\"> </a></td><td>population variance</td><td><div><p>Variance of the values in the referenced set of values, computed over the population.</p>\n</div></td><td>23451</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  VARIANCE.S<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-VARIANCE.46S\"> </a></td><td>sample variance</td><td><div><p>Variance of the values in the referenced set of values, computed over a sample of the population.</p>\n</div></td><td>23449</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">_VerificationMethod<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-_VerificationMethod\"> </a></td><td>VerificationMethod</td><td/><td>21512</td><td>active</td><td/><td>true</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  VDOC<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-VDOC\"> </a></td><td>document verification</td><td><div><p>Verification by means of document.</p>\n<p><em>Example:</em> Fax, letter, attachment to e-mail.</p>\n</div></td><td>21515</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  VREG<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-VREG\"> </a></td><td>registry verification</td><td><div><p>verification by means of a response to an electronic query</p>\n<p><em>Example:</em> query message to a Covered Party registry application or Coverage Administrator.</p>\n</div></td><td>21514</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  VTOKEN<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-VTOKEN\"> </a></td><td>electronic token verification</td><td><div><p>Verification by means of electronic token.</p>\n<p><em>Example:</em> smartcard, magnetic swipe card, RFID device.</p>\n</div></td><td>21513</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  VVOICE<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-VVOICE\"> </a></td><td>voice-based verification</td><td><div><p>Verification by means of voice.</p>\n<p><em>Example:</em> By speaking with or calling the Coverage Administrator or Covered Party</p>\n</div></td><td>21516</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">0001<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-0001\"> </a></td><td>Complement fixation</td><td><div><p>Complement fixation</p>\n</div></td><td>14080</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">0002<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-0002\"> </a></td><td>Computed axial tomography</td><td><div><p>Computed axial tomography</p>\n</div></td><td>14081</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">0003<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-0003\"> </a></td><td>HLAR agar test</td><td><div><p>Susceptibility, High Level Aminoglycoside Resistance agar test</p>\n</div></td><td>14082</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">0004<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-0004\"> </a></td><td>Macroscopic observation</td><td><div><p>Visual, Macroscopic observation</p>\n</div></td><td>14083</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">0005<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-0005\"> </a></td><td>Magnetic resonance</td><td><div><p>Computed, Magnetic resonance</p>\n</div></td><td>14084</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">0006<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-0006\"> </a></td><td>Morphometry</td><td><div><p>Computed, Morphometry</p>\n</div></td><td>14085</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">0007<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-0007\"> </a></td><td>Positron emission tomography</td><td><div><p>Computed, Positron emission tomography</p>\n</div></td><td>14086</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">0008<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-0008\"> </a></td><td>SAMHSA confirmation</td><td><div><p>SAMHSA drug assay confirmation</p>\n</div></td><td>14087</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">0009<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-0009\"> </a></td><td>SAMHSA screening</td><td><div><p>SAMHSA drug assay screening</p>\n</div></td><td>14088</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">0010<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-0010\"> </a></td><td>Serum Neutralization</td><td><div><p>Serum Neutralization</p>\n</div></td><td>14089</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">0011<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-0011\"> </a></td><td>Titration</td><td><div><p>Titration</p>\n</div></td><td>14090</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">0012<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-0012\"> </a></td><td>Ultrasound</td><td><div><p>Ultrasound</p>\n</div></td><td>14091</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">0013<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-0013\"> </a></td><td>X-ray crystallography</td><td><div><p>X-ray crystallography</p>\n</div></td><td>14092</td><td>active</td><td/><td/></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">0014<a name=\"v3-ObservationMethod-0014\"> </a></td><td>Agglutination</td><td><div><p>Agglutination</p>\n</div></td><td>